      {
        "text": "##### Type\nElectrolyte solution [no schedule]\n\n- **High-risk medication**\n\n##### Presentations\n2.5g in 5 ml (50% solution) – glass ampoule\n\n##### Actions\nMagnesium is the second most abundant intracellular cation. Less than 1% is present in extracellular fluid. Magnesium is involved in the processes regulating sodium and potassium movement across cell membranes and, as such, it may promote myocardial cell membrane stability.\n\n#### Uses\n\n- Torsades de pointes / polymorphic VT **- ICP only**\n\n- Refractory VF (3rd drug) **- ICP only**\n\n- Any seizure activity, or acute history of seizure activity, in patients with >20/40 gestation\n\n- Symptomatic pre-eclampsia – hypertensive pregnant patient (20/40 to 6/52 post partum) presenting as unwell (altered LOC, headache, abdominal pain, visual disturbances, etc.) **- ICP only**\n\n#### Adverse Effects\nRare – more common if serum magnesium is normal:\n\n- Respiratory depression\n\n- Nausea and vomiting\n\n- Hypotension\n\n- Confusion\n\n- Bradycardia\n\n#### Contraindications\n\n- AV block\n\n- Renal failure\n\n- Hepatic failure\n\n#### Precautions\nMyasthenia gravis\n\n#### Pregnancy and Breastfeeding##### Pregnancy\n- Safe to use\n\n##### Breastfeeding\n- Safe to use\n\n#### Doses##### Adult\n- **ICP: ****With cardiac output: **2.5g IV/IO \n- Diluted up to 10ml with normal saline\n- Given over 5 minutes. \n\n- **ICP: ****Refractory VF: **2.5g IV/IO \n- Over 30-60 seconds \n- **ICP: ****Torsades de pointes: **2.5g IV/IO \n- Over 30-60 seconds \n- **ICP: ****Pre-eclampsia: **2.5g IV/IO via Springfusor \n- Made up to 7ml total volume with normal saline (7ml will run over 10 minutes).\n- **Seizures due to eclampsia: **\n- 2.5g IV/IO over 30-60 seconds\n- Followed by 2.5g IV/IO via Springfusor - Made up to 7ml total volume with normal saline (7ml will run over 10 minutes).##### Paediatric\n- Dose is 50mg/kg (to max of 2.5g)\n- Dilute entire ampoule up to 10ml = 250mg/ml. Discard excess.\n- **With cardiac output: **Give calculated dose IV/IO over 3 – 5 minutes.\n- **No cardiac output: **Give calculated dose IV/IO over 30 – 60 seconds.\n#### Special Notes\n- Prolonged hypotension post-magnesium administration – if unresponsive to fluids, patient may be treated with IV calcium.",
